-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Pomalca, Relapasa, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-16T21:38:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/peru-stocks-buenaventura-pomalca-relapasa-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.4 percent to 22,360.79. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 0.8 percent to 2,819.05.  Mining and industrial stocks gained as fourth-quarter
earnings topped analysts’ estimates, said  Daniel Romero , an
analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose for the first day in eight, gaining 2.4 percent
to 3 soles.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, advanced 2.3 percent to
$40.50.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, climbed 2 percent to 1 sol as crude rose to a six-week
high in New York.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s
biggest copper producer, gained 1.7 percent to $32.85.  Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar producer, rose
1.7 percent to 60 centimos after sugar futures advanced for a
second session in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
